-- Santiago's Metro subscribes $800 mln in loans for expansion
-- By Anthony Esposito
-- Thu Dec 18, 2014 03:03PM EST
-- None



SANTIAGO, Dec 18 (Reuters) - The metro train system servicing Chile's capital has subscribed $800 million in loans with a syndicate of international banks to finance expansion work, the state-owned transport company said on Thursday.

A syndicate of banks headed by Sumitomo Mitsui Bank Corp will lend Metro $250 million, and a second syndicate led by BNP Paribas <BNPP.PA> will loan another $550 million.